# Managed unit inventory consumed by scripts/deploy.sh.
#
# deploy.sh watches a UNIT_SET for an active-state regression across a deploy: a
# unit that was active BEFORE and is not active AFTER fails the deploy and
# triggers rollback. The effective UNIT_SET is the union of:
#   (a) BACKEND units DERIVED FROM .env — their names are .env variables
#       (XRAY_SERVICE_NAME, SOCKS5_SERVICE_NAME, MTPROTO_SERVICE_NAME,
#        HYSTERIA2_SERVICE_NAME, HYSTERIA2_AUTH_SERVICE_NAME) and each protocol is
#       included only when its *_ENABLED gate is true. Protocols are MODULAR: an
#       admin toggles them at runtime, so a missing backend unit is NORMAL, not an
#       error. deploy.sh reads these from .env; do NOT list them here.
#   (b) the names listed in THIS file, and
#   (c) the basenames of every deploy/*.service shipped on origin/main
#       (excluding *.example.service).
#
# List here ONLY the data-plane / system units the bot depends on that have NO
# .env variable — i.e. things that cannot be derived from source (a). Repo-shipped
# units come from (c) automatically; the WARP data-plane units below are listed
# for explicitness even where a deploy/*.service also ships them.
#
# One unit name per line; '#' starts a comment. deploy.sh hard-fails at start if
# this file is missing (it never substitutes a silent default).
#
# IMPORTANT: verify every name against the actual host with
# `systemctl show -p LoadState --value <unit>` (NOT `systemctl list-unit-files`,
# which does not list template instances such as awg-quick@awg0). A name not
# loaded on the host is reported (WARN); the reverse "running-but-not-watched"
# check in the Phase 1 report is the real guard against a rename or typo.

# --- WARP / AmneziaWG data-plane units (no .env variable) ---
awg-quick@awg0.service          # AWG server interface (template instance)
awg-quick@out-warp.service      # WARP egress interface (template instance)
vpnbot-hy2-warp-mark.service    # Hysteria2 -> WARP fwmark tagging
warp-routes.service             # WARP policy routes (also shipped as deploy/*.service)
warp-failsafe.service           # WARP kill-switch (also shipped as deploy/*.service)
vpn-bot-warp-split.service      # WARP split-tunnel state (also shipped as deploy/*.service)
